Package msvc.exceptions

Class MSVCEHInfo

java.lang.Object
msvc.exceptions.MSVCEHInfo
public class MSVCEHInfo extends Object
Represents the exception handling information for Microsoft Visual C++-compiled binaries that can be derived from the various EH-related data structures used.

  • Constructor Details

    • MSVCEHInfo

      public MSVCEHInfo(int magicNumber, int bbtFlags, int maxState, ghidra.program.model.address.Address pUnwindMap, int nTryBlocks, ghidra.program.model.address.Address pTryBlockMap, int nIPMapEntries, ghidra.program.model.address.Address pIPToStateMap, ghidra.program.model.address.Address pESTypeList, int ehFlags, UnwindMap unwindMap, List<TryBlockMapEntry> tryBlockMapEntries)
      Creates an MSVCEHInfo instance which represents the FuncInfo data structure, extended with information and objects derived from the data structures linked to FuncInfo.
      Parameters:
      magicNumber - The "compiler version identifier" (but really more an identifier of which kinds of EH are supported).
      bbtFlags - "Flags that may be set by BBT processing."
      maxState - Number of entries in the unwind map.
      pUnwindMap - Address of the unwind map.
      nTryBlocks - Number of try blocks.
      pTryBlockMap - Address of the TryBlockMap.
      nIPMapEntries - "Number of IP-to-state map entries."
      pIPToStateMap - Address of the "IP-to-state map".
      pESTypeList - Address of the ESTypeList.
      ehFlags - Flags for some specific EH-related features.
      unwindMap - An UnwindMap instance, derived from the linked UnwindMap data structure.
      tryBlockMapEntries - The list of TryBlockMapEntries, derived from the linked TryBlockMap data structure.

  • Method Details

    • analyze

      public void analyze() throws ghidra.program.model.data.InvalidDataTypeException
      Tries to determine the try/catch block layout based on the tryBlockMapEntries and the unwindMap.
      Throws:
      ghidra.program.model.data.InvalidDataTypeException - If there is a state mismatch or other processing error.

    • getTryCatchBlockOverview

      public static List<String> getTryCatchBlockOverview(List<TryBlockMapEntry> outerTryBlockMapEntries, String header)
      Generates a list of strings with an overview of the (possibly nested) try/catch block layout from the given TryBlockMapEntries.
      Parameters:
      outerTryBlockMapEntries - The list of TryBlockMapEntries to derive the layout overview from.
      header - A header line to include as the first line to the overview.
      Returns:
      A list of strings with the try/catch block layout.

    • determineLayout

      public static ArrayList<TryBlockMapEntry> determineLayout(List<TryBlockMapEntry> tryBlockMapEntries)
      Determines the layout of the try/catch blocks as much as possible just from TryBlockMapEntries.
      Parameters:
      tryBlockMapEntries - The TryBlockMapEntries from which to derive the try/catch layout.
      Returns:
      A list of 'outer' TryBlockMapEntries; any nested entries will have been added as such to these outer ones.

    • recurse

      public static void recurse(TryBlockMapEntry current, ITryCatch parent, HashSet<Integer> knownStates, UnwindMap unwindMap, String prefix) throws ghidra.program.model.data.InvalidDataTypeException
      Recursively determines nested try and catch block layout starting from a given TryBlockMapEntry, incorporating unwind information to find catch block states and to double-check try block states.
      Parameters:
      current - The current TryBlockMapEntry being processed.
      parent - The parent (TryBlock or CatchHandler) for current; may be null if current is the root.
      knownStates - The set of 'known' states (states already matched to a try or catch block).
      unwindMap - An UnwindMap containing state transition information.
      prefix - A string prefix used for logging to indicate the level of recursion (depth).
      Throws:
      ghidra.program.model.data.InvalidDataTypeException - If there is a state mismatch or other processing error.
